text: I went on a Sunday evening, its a decent park, not very crowded, good place to wind down. Has a small play area for kids and also a small tennis court. Thereâ€™s benches and also few huts, big tamarind trees gives some shading from the bright sun.

Park is spacious. It has decent amount of play areas for kids. There is a good length for walking around the park. It has two rest room facilities. There are a few sitout with good shade to take rest. There is a basket ball court, a badminton court. There are a lot of trees and good amount of shade. You can come with a mat, spend some time with family on a weekend.
Average neighborhood park. Good for morning and evening walk if you live around here. Not worth to make a special trip to visit.
